		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">notinasia wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Is it a derivative of the 6502?</div><br />Absolutely not.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">how does it send images to the TV</div><br />I believe one of the pins of the chip outputs a composite video signal, which is the result of all the PPU logic.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">or communicate with the CPU?</div>
<br />The PPU doesn't have to know about the CPU, but programs running on the CPU "talk" to the PPU by using memory-mapped registers.

		

